  "text": "As we continue to debate how we may overcome these issues, it is important to remember that previous concerns about greater transparency in medical practice, such as improving patient access to their doctors' notes, have almost always led to increased patient satisfaction and compliance with their medical care. [CITATION_1] Ensuring elevated surgical quality consistently across all providers is complex. But as evidence grows on how quality can be evaluated and enhanced through operative video, its role must be considered thoughtfully in the context of \"what is best for our patients?\" Using this as our guiding principle, we believe the next driver for surgical quality can be the operating room video camera.",
